<section>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Description of Data is an important chapter in statistics that deals with
        collecting, organizing, presenting, and summarizing data in a meaningful way.
        It helps in understanding large sets of data easily.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Types of Data</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Primary Data:</b> Data collected for the first time.</li>
        <li><b>Secondary Data:</b> Data collected from existing sources.</li>
        <li><b>Qualitative Data:</b> Descriptive data (e.g., gender, color).</li>
        <li><b>Quantitative Data:</b> Numerical data (e.g., marks, height).</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Methods of Data Representation</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Tabular Representation</li>
        <li>Bar Graph</li>
        <li>Histogram</li>
        <li>Pie Chart</li>
        <li>Frequency Polygon</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Measures of Central Tendency</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Mean:</b> Average of the data values.</li>
        <li><b>Median:</b> Middle value of arranged data.</li>
        <li><b>Mode:</b> Most frequently occurring value.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Measures of Dispersion</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Range</li>
        <li>Mean Deviation</li>
        <li>Variance</li>
        <li>Standard Deviation</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Applications of Description of Data</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Used in education to analyze student performance</li>
        <li>Used in business for decision making</li>
        <li>Used in research and surveys</li>
        <li>Used in economics and social sciences</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
        The description of data helps us understand information clearly and make
        better decisions. It is an essential part of statistics and has wide
        applications in daily life.
    </p>
</section>

